Rename row and col names

getName <- function(x){
  v <- unlist(strsplit(x, '\\.'))
  name <- paste0(v[1], '-', v[2])
  return(name)
}
getName2 <- function(x){
  w <- unlist(strsplit(x, '\\-'))
  w2 <- w[1]
  return(w2)
}

Protein_missdf <- Protein_match2 %>%
  gather(key = "key", value = "val") %>%
  mutate(is.missing = is.na(val)) %>%
  group_by(key, is.missing) %>%
  summarise(num.missing = n()) %>%
  filter(is.missing==T) %>%
  select(-is.missing) %>%
  arrange(desc(num.missing))
CNA_missdf <- CNA_match2 %>%
  gather(key = "key", value = "val") %>%
  mutate(is.missing = is.na(val)) %>%
  group_by(key, is.missing) %>%
  summarise(num.missing = n()) %>%
  filter(is.missing==T) %>%
  select(-is.missing) %>%
  arrange(desc(num.missing))
RNA_missdf <- RNA_match2 %>%
  gather(key = "key", value = "val") %>%
  mutate(is.missing = is.na(val)) %>%
  group_by(key, is.missing) %>%
  summarise(num.missing = n()) %>%
  filter(is.missing==T) %>%
  select(-is.missing) %>%
  arrange(desc(num.missing))
Protein_missdf %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_bar(aes(x=reorder(key, -num.missing), y=num.missing), stat = 'identity') +
  labs(x='Gene', y="number of missing values", title='Number of missing values') +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

RNA_missdf %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_bar(aes(x=reorder(key, -num.missing), y=num.missing), stat = 'identity') +
  labs(x='Gene', y="number of missing values", title='Number of missing values') +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

# 数据导入
setwd('/Users/dengshuyang/Desktop/Bioinfo2019/Breast_project/')
Protein_Breast <- read.csv('Protein_Breast_2.csv', stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
RNA_Breast <- read.csv('RNA_Breast_2.csv', stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
CNA_Breast <- read.csv('CNA_Breast_2.csv', stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
pam50_genes <- read.csv('pam50_genes.csv', stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
# 数据筛选
Protein_Breast <- merge(pam50_genes, Protein_Breast, by.y = 'X', by.x = 'gene') #inner join if don't use all.x=TRUE
RNA_Breast <- merge(pam50_genes, RNA_Breast, by.y = 'X', by.x = 'gene', all.x = TRUE)
CNA_Breast <- merge(pam50_genes, CNA_Breast, by.y='X', by.x='gene')
# 数据转换
row.names(Protein_Breast) <- Protein_Breast$gene
Protein_Breast <- select(Protein_Breast, -gene) 
Protein_Breast <- as.matrix(Protein_Breast)

row.names(RNA_Breast) <- RNA_Breast$gene
RNA_Breast <- select(RNA_Breast, -gene)
RNA_Breast <- as.matrix(RNA_Breast)

rownames(CNA_Breast) <- CNA_Breast$gene
CNA_Breast <- select(CNA_Breast, -gene)
CNA_Breast <- as.matrix(CNA_Breast)

making heatmap

resource: https://wiki.bits.vib.be/index.php/Use_pheatmap_to_draw_heat_maps_in_R

# Protein-protein
col.pal <- brewer.pal(9,"Blues")
drows1 <- "euclidean"
dcols1 <- "euclidean"

hm.parameters <- list(Protein_Breast, 
  color = col.pal,
  cellwidth = 4, cellheight = 5, scale = "none",
  treeheight_row = 200,
  kmeans_k = NA,
  show_rownames = T, show_colnames = T,
  main = "Protein-Protein heatmap",
  clustering_method = "average",
  cluster_rows = TRUE, cluster_cols = TRUE,
  clustering_distance_rows = drows1, 
  clustering_distance_cols = dcols1,
  fontsize = 5
  )
do.call("pheatmap", hm.parameters)

#RNA-RNA

hm.parameters2 <- list(RNA_Breast, 
  color = col.pal,
  cellwidth = 4, cellheight = 5, scale = 'column',
  treeheight_row = 200,
  kmeans_k = NA,
  show_rownames = T, show_colnames = T,
  main = "Protein-Protein heatmap",
  clustering_method = "average",
  cluster_rows = TRUE, cluster_cols = TRUE,
  clustering_distance_rows = drows1, 
  clustering_distance_cols = dcols1,
  fontsize = 5)
do.call("pheatmap", hm.parameters2)

#CNA-CNA

hm.parameters3 <- list(CNA_Breast, 
  color = col.pal,
  cellwidth = 4, cellheight = 5, scale = "none",
  treeheight_row = 200,
  kmeans_k = NA,
  show_rownames = T, show_colnames = T,
  main = "Protein-Protein heatmap",
  clustering_method = "average",
  cluster_rows = TRUE, cluster_cols = TRUE,
  clustering_distance_rows = drows1, 
  clustering_distance_cols = dcols1,
  fontsize=5)
do.call("pheatmap", hm.parameters3)

Protein_Breast <- read.csv('Protein_Breast_2.csv', stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
RNA_Breast <- read.csv('RNA_Breast_2.csv', stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
CNA_Breast <- read.csv('CNA_Breast_2.csv', stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
pam50_genes <- read.csv('pam50_genes.csv', stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

colnames(Protein_Breast) <- paste0(colnames(Protein_Breast), '_pro')
colnames(RNA_Breast) <- paste0(colnames(RNA_Breast), '_rna')

pro_rna <- merge(pam50_genes, Protein_Breast, by.x = 'gene', by.y = 'X_pro', all.x = TRUE)
pro_rna <- merge(pro_rna, RNA_Breast, by.x = 'gene', by.y = 'X_rna', all.x = TRUE)

row.names(pro_rna) <- pro_rna$gene
pro_rna <- select(pro_rna, -gene)
pro_rna <- as.matrix(pro_rna)

k means, remove na

Protein_Breast <- na.omit(Protein_Breast) maxclust <- 5 for(maxclust in c(2:maxclust)) {

main <- paste(“result for”, maxclust, " clusters“, sep=”“) hmx.parameters5 <- list(Protein_Breast, color = col.pal, cellwidth = 4, cellheight = 5, scale =”none“, treeheight_row = 200, kmeans_k = maxclust, show_rownames = T, show_colnames = T, main = main, clustering_method =”average“, cluster_rows = TRUE, cluster_cols = TRUE, clustering_distance_rows = drows1, clustering_distance_cols = dcols1) kmean.hm <- do.call(”pheatmap“, hmx.parameters5) do.call(”pheatmap“, hmx.parameters5) clustnum <- kmean.hm[[“kmeans”]][[“cluster”]] clustered.Protein_Breast <- cbind(Protein_Breast, clustnum) last <- ncol(clustered.Protein_Breast)-1 }

filename <- paste(“Clustered.for.”, maxclust, “-clusters.tsv”, sep=“”) outfile <- paste(basedir, filename, sep=“/”)

write.table(clustered.Protein_Breast, file=outfile, quote = FALSE, sep=“”, col.names = T, row.names = T)

# plot ‘maxclust’ cluster detailed heatmap’s clustered.Protein_Breast <- as.data.frame(clustered.Protein_Breast)

for (clust in 1:maxclust){ # sample data cluster <- subset(clustered.Protein_Breast, clustered.Protein_Breast$clustnum==clust)[1:last]

# prepare output
filename <- paste("cluster.", clust, "_of_", maxclust,".pdf", sep="")
outfile <- paste(basedir, filename, sep="/")

main <- paste("cluster #", clust, " of #", maxclust, sep="")

cluster.parameters6 <- list(cluster,
                           color = col.pal,
                           cellwidth = 4, cellheight = 5,
                           scale = "none",
                           treeheight_row = 200,
                           kmeans_k = NA,
                           show_rownames = T, show_colnames = T, 
                           main = main,
                           clustering_method = "average",
                           cluster_rows = TRUE, cluster_cols = TRUE,
                           clustering_distance_rows = drows1,
                           clustering_distance_cols = dcols1)
do.call("pheatmap", cluster.parameters6)
do.call("pheatmap", c(cluster.parameters6, filename=outfile))

} }

第三幅图

=====================

Protein_Breast <- read.csv(‘Protein_Breast.csv’, stringsAsFactors = FALSE) RNA_Breast <- read.csv(‘RNA_Breast.csv’, stringsAsFactors = FALSE) pam50_genes <- read.csv(‘pam50_genes.csv’, stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

colnames(Protein_Breast) <- paste0(colnames(Protein_Breast), ’_pro’) colnames(RNA_Breast) <- paste0(colnames(RNA_Breast), ’_rna’)

data <- merge(pam50_genes, Protein_Breast, by.x = ‘gene’, by.y = ‘X_pro’, all.x = TRUE) data <- merge(data, RNA_Breast, by.x = ‘gene’, by.y = ‘X_rna’, all.x = TRUE)

row.names(data) <- data$gene data <- select(data, -gene) data <- as.matrix(data)

rc <- rainbow(nrow(data), start = 0, end = .3) cc <- rainbow(ncol(data), start = 0, end = .3) hv <- heatmap( data, col = cm.colors(256), scale = “column”, RowSideColors = rc, ColSideColors = cc, margins = c(5,10), xlab = " “, ylab =” “, main =”data" )
